        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>THE JEWISH MESSENGER&#44;<lb/>
                2 WEST 14<hi rend="sup">th</hi> STREET&#44;<lb/></p>
                
            <p>New York&#44; Aug 13&#91;&#44;&#93; 1885.<lb/></p>
                
            <p>Dear Mr. Morais&#58;<lb/></p>
            <p>Proofs arrived just in<lb/>time for  revision. Shall insert half<lb/> of article this week&#8212;did not think<lb/> it would be so long. It is curious<lb/> that a Boston professor &#40;Warren&#41; should<lb/> have lately written a book w&#91;ith&#93; location<lb/> of Paradise&#44; &#38; puts it in North<lb/> Pole&#44; instead of Equator.<lb/></p>
            <p>I have a consecration<lb/> of Synag. Sunday in this city &#38; one<lb/> on Aug. 30<hi rend="sup">th</hi> in Brooklyn. In the latter&#44;<lb/> they wanted a new prayerbook &#38;<lb/> some wished Minhag America. I managed<lb/> to have Minhag Jastrow favored <lb/> instead. With these new conserv.<lb/> Synag. being started&#44; it is a<lb/> pity that there is no authorized<lb/> abridged ritual. My only  radical<lb/>ism is in reference to the<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>synag. service. With the reaction<lb/> now in favor of conservatism&#44; a<lb/> good honest revised liturgy would<lb/> be a blessing&#44; especially if the<lb/> principle of selection be allowed.<lb/> Let the new book contain everything&#44;<lb/> but let much be <hi rend="underline">optional</hi>. I<lb/> know the difficulty&#58; but it is<lb/> impossible to inspire enthus<lb/> iasm among the young when<lb/> the worship is unduly protracted. The<lb/> original elements of our<lb/> prayer book are so simple<lb/> &#38; sublime that it is a pity<lb/> we sacrifice them. However&#44;<lb/> I don&#39;t write this to get a<lb/> reply&#44; but jot down the<lb/> thought as it occurs.<lb/></p>
            <p>With regards&#44;<lb/>
                A.S. Isaacs<lb/></p>
                <p>Extra copies<lb/> will be forwarded.<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
